# Klyashevo, Chishminsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Klyashevo (, , Keläş) is a rural locality (a selo) in Arovsky Selsoviet, Chishminsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The rural locality has 18 streets and, as of 2010, a population of 560.
Geography
Klyashevo is located 23 km east of Chishmy, the district's administrative centre. Dubrava is the nearest rural locality.
